6 Section 2. KRS 610.340 is amended to read as follows:
7 (1) (a) Unless a specific provision of KRS Chapters 600 to 645 specifies otherwise,
8 all juvenile court records of any nature generated pursuant to KRS Chapters
9 600 to 645 by any agency or instrumentality, public or private, shall be
10 deemed to be confidential and shall not be disclosed except to the child,
11 parent, victims, or other persons authorized to attend a juvenile court hearing
12 pursuant to KRS 610.070 unless ordered by the court for good cause.
13 (b) Juvenile court records which contain information pertaining to arrests,
14 petitions, adjudications, and dispositions of a child may be disclosed to
15 victims or other persons authorized to attend a juvenile court hearing pursuant
16 to KRS 610.070.
17 (c) Release of the child's treatment, medical, mental, or psychological records is
18 prohibited unless presented as evidence in Circuit Court. Any records
19 resulting from the child's prior abuse and neglect under Title IV-E or Title IV-
20 B of the Federal Social Security Act shall not be disclosed to victims or other
21 persons authorized to attend a juvenile court hearing pursuant to KRS
22 610.070.
23 (d) Victim access under this subsection to juvenile court records shall include
24 access to records of adjudications that occurred prior to July 15, 1998.
25 (2) The provisions of this section shall not apply to public officers or employees
26 engaged in the investigation of and in the prosecution of cases under KRS Chapters
27 600 to 645 or other portions of the Kentucky Revised Statutes. Any record obtained
